=head1 DESCRIPTION

Stores the configuration information for a visual helper element for a
form. A sectional element can be a header, a text block, or a divider.
These elements are static and not associated with any data.

=head1 ATTRIBUTES


=head2 Excluded => Bool

Excludes a sectional element that was generated by default for a
specified data model.


=head2 Level => Int

Specifies the size of the font for a C<Heading> sectional element.
Valid values are C<1 | 2 | 3 | 4 | 5 | 6>.


=head2 Orientation => Str

Specifies the orientation for a C<Divider> sectional element. Valid
values are C<horizontal> or C<vertical>.


=head2 Position => L<Paws::AmplifyUIBuilder::FieldPosition>

Specifies the position of the text in a field for a C<Text> sectional
element.


=head2 Text => Str

The text for a C<Text> sectional element.


=head2 B<REQUIRED> Type => Str

The type of sectional element. Valid values are C<Heading>, C<Text>,
and C<Divider>.



